<p>
<seg id=1> According to the ground controllers for the non-stop around the world hot air balloon attempt, the three flyers on the hot air balloon should fly out of China's air space on Wednesday.  They are heading east to cross the Pacific Ocean. </seg>
<seg id=2> On Tuesday, the three men team in the highflying hot air balloon deviated from the flying corridor stipulated by China and got themselves in political troubles. </seg>
<seg id=3> Chinese officials once ordered them to land in Tibet, a region governed by China.  However, China cancelled the order after U.S. and British diplomats took up the issue with Chinese officials. </seg>
